* water for agriculture;
* water for energy;
* water for industry;
* water for tourism and recreation; and
* water for  other uses.

55.
* If the declaration of a water management area results in or requires the acquisition of land, every such acquisition, including the award of compensation and appeals related thereto shall be conducted in accordance with the Land Act of Bhutan.
* The Commission may prescribe limitations to be observed within a water management area, which may include, among others, a prohibition or limitation:
	* on the abstraction of water;
	* on the erection of any structures;
	* on the application or storage of any chemicals, including pesticides or fertilisers;
	* on the alteration of existing land contours, including any grading or construction of roads or cultivation of crops;
	* including the felling of trees, the removal of riparian growth or the use of wetland resources;

68.
* Order specifying actions the violators must undertake to come into compliance;
* Order to take mitigative, corrective or restorative measures as may be deemed necessary to prevent further damage being caused to human health and/ or environment;

ལྷན་ཚོགས་དང་ ཚད་ལྡན་དབང་འཛིན་ཚུ་གིས་ བཅའ་ཁྲིམས་འདིའམ་ འདིའི་དགོངས་ དོན་ལས་འགལ་བའི་ བདག་སྐྱོང་གི་ཉེས་བྱ་ཚུ་ དབྱེ་དཔྱད་འབད་དེ་ གྲོས་ཐག་བཅད་ ཆོག། བདག་སྐྱོང་གི་ཉེས་བྱའི་གྲངས་སུ་ གཤམ་གསལ་ལས་གཅིག་ ཡང་ན་ དེ་ལས་ མང་མ་ཚུདཔ་ཨིན་:
* Payment of a fine not exceeding twelve man-months of the National minimum wage;
	* Reimbursement of any costs incurred by an Authority due to offendersâ failure to take the notified measures in time;
	* Payment of compensatory costs for rectifying any damage to the environment, persons or property caused by the offence;
	* Suspension or revocation of an Environment Clearance under this Act;
	* A fine equivalent to ten man-months as per the minimum wage per day in the event of the offence being continued after stop order till the day such offence is discontinued; and
	* Failure to comply with the stop order, an activity shall be shut down without compensation.
	* The magnitude of the offence;
	* The frequency of the offence;

ཁྲིམས་འཆལ་གྱི་དོན་ལུ་ བདག་སྐྱོང་གི་ཉེས་ཆད་བཀལ་བའི་སྐབས་ལུ་ འབྲེལ་ཡོད་དབང་ འཛིན་ཚུ་གིས་ འོག་གི་གནད་དོན་ཚུ་ལུ་ བརྩི་འཇོག་འབད་དགོ: ཀ) གནོད་འགེལ་གྱི་ཚབས་ཆེ་ཆུང་། ཁ) གནོད་འགེལ་གྱི་དུས་ཐེངས།
* Actual or potential impact on the environment and human health;
* The culpability of the offender;
* The extent of the achieved or intended economic advantage from the  offence; and
* The need to deter future violations of the Act and regulations by the same or other persons.

74.
* Abstracts water resource without obtaining an Environmental Clearance as required under this Act;
* Discharge effluents without obtaining an Environmental Clearance as required under this Act;
* Activities in contravention with the provisions of Section 45(a) and (b) of this Act; and
* Other activities leading to degradation of watershed and catchment areas.
* Endangerment of public water source;
* Failure to comply with the terms and conditions of an Environmental Clearance;
* Failure to comply with administrative sanctions; and
